'''Janae Bakken''' is an [[Americans|American]] television producer and screenwriter best known for her work on the television series ''[[Scrubs (TV series)|Scrubs]]''.
The [[Minneapolis, Minnesota]]-born Bakken has worked on ''[[Scrubs (TV series)|Scrubs]]'' since 2001, as a writer, and in 2002 served as a story editor, but was promoted and until 2004, served as an executive story editor. From there to 2005, she worked as a co-producer and in 2006 became a producer, and between 2006 and 2007 was supervising producer of twenty episodes. Aside from ''Scrubs'', she has written the 2005 film ''[[Artistic License (film)|Artistic License]]'' and two episodes during the third season of ''[[Malcolm in the Middle]]''.
She once commented that almost all of the ideas brought into and discussed in the ''Scrubs''' writers' room were parallel to the writers' own lives, and that she specifically had suggested a number of storylines and subplots based on her own life.<ref>[http://odeo.com/audio/11899733/view Sarah Chalke (Eliot) and Janae Bakken (writer) comment on "MY COLD SHOWER"], ODEO.com; retrieved November 9, 2007.</ref><ref>Ken P. (October 27, 2005) [http://au.movies.ign.com/articles/650/650103p1.html "''Scrubs'' Bios: Meet and greet"], au.movies.ign.com; retrieved November 9, 2007.</ref> An alumna of [[Northwestern University]]<ref>[http://www.communication.northwestern.edu/creative/alumni/ Alumni] ''School of Communication at Northwestern''; retrieved November 9, 2007.</ref> she has held a number of lectures at their School of Communication.<ref>[http://www.communication.northwestern.edu/events/lectures/tv/ Television Writing Panel: Creative Writing for the Media], Northwestern University School of Communication website; retrieved November 9, 2007.</ref>
==Personal life== She married actor Michael Cotter on April 24, 2004;<ref>[http://www.northwestern.edu/magazine/northwestern/summer2005/classnotes/marriages.htm Marriages], Summer 2005, ''Northwestern University''; retrieved November 9, 2007.</ref> the couple has one child.<ref>[http://www.variety.com/article/VR1117982255.html?categoryid=26&cs=1 Profile], variety.com, March 11, 2008; retrieved September 27, 2008.</ref>
